  "texts": [
    "You will of course ask the question: if Θ is infinite, what will the log(M) term be replaced with?",
    "In PAC-Bayes bounds, this term will be replaced by the Kullback-Leibler divergence between ρ and a fixed π on Θ (the prior).",
    "Definition 1.2.",
    "Given two probability measures µ and ν in P(Θ), the Kullback-Leibler (or simply KL) divergence between µ and ν is",
    "if µ has a density dµ dν with respect to ν, and KL(µ∥ν) = +∞ otherwise. 5"
  ],
